Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Place Order (UC2), Validate Payment Details (UC5), the <<include>> relationship from UC2 to UC5
   Explanation: "Validate Payment Details" (UC5) is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Place Order" / UC2). It is not associated with any actor directly, it does not include or extend any other use case, it is not extended by any other use case, and it is not involved in any generalization. "Validate Payment Details" does not represent a complete, independently valuable service to any actor — it is merely a sub-step of placing an order that has been decomposed out unnecessarily. This constitutes the Functional Decomposition antipattern via the include relationship.
